Police fired tear gas into crowds Friday as violent clashes between authorities and anti-government protesters. Hours ahead of what are expected to be massive anti-government protests, the Internet went dark in parts of Egypt early Friday. Text messaging and cell phone services appeared to be blocked. People in Egypt are under governmental siege.
